The three police officers are charged in connection with the killing of teenager Nathaniel Julies. Their formal bail bid will continue on Monday. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The three police officers who stand accused of killing 16-year-old Nathaniel Julies will only know if their bail application is successful on Monday morning. The trio is charged in connection with the killing of the Eldorado Park teenager. READ: Nathaniel Julies case: Lawyer blames 'dysfunctional' police system The accused officers will remain in custody. Julies was shot last month, sparking outrage among community members, who took to the streets in protest.